Package: bioconverter
Type: Package
Title: Universal Bioinformatics Data Converter for Multi-Omics Formats
Version: 0.1.1
Authors@R: c(
    person("Bioinformatics Data Converter", "Contributors", 
           email = "contributors@example.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
    )
Description: A comprehensive toolkit for converting various bioinformatics 
    data formats to unified standard formats. Supports genomics (GWAS, VCF),
    transcriptomics (RNA-seq), proteomics, and metabolomics data. Features
    interactive column mapping, automatic format detection, and efficient 
    processing of gigabyte-scale files through chunking.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends:
    R (>= 3.6.0)
Imports:
    reticulate (>= 1.20),
    readr (>= 2.0.0),
    tibble (>= 3.0.0)
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    knitr,
    rmarkdown
SystemRequirements: Python (>= 3.8) with bioconverter package installed (pip install bioconverter)
RoxygenNote: 7.2.0
VignetteBuilder: knitr
URL: https://github.com/Jeblqr/bioConv, https://pypi.org/project/bioconverter/
BugReports: https://github.com/Jeblqr/bioConv/issues
